  PREMIUM ASSURED SHORTHOLD TENANCY AGREEMENT
  England Only - Solicitor-Grade Premium Edition

  LEGAL NOTE: This Assured Shorthold Tenancy (AST) agreement applies to England ONLY.
  Premium includes: detailed guarantor provisions, HMO terms, late payment, key schedule,
  maintenance, emergency procedures, and enhanced move-in/out checklists.

  STRUCTURE:
  1. Cover/Title
  2. Parties (including Guarantor if applicable)
  3. Definitions & Interpretation
  4. Core Clauses (Property, Term, Rent, Deposit, Obligations)
  5. Premium Clauses (Late Payment, Access, Maintenance)
  6. Guarantor Agreement (if applicable)
  7. Signatures
  8. Schedules (1-7 with premium additions)
  ============================================================================
--}}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-GB">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Premium Assured Shorthold Tenancy Agreement</title>
  <style>
    @page { size: A4; margin: 25mm 20mm; }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: 'Georgia', 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.5; color: #1a1a1a; background: white; }
    h1, h2, h3, h4 { font-family: 'Arial', 'Helvetica', sans-serif; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 0; page-break-after: avoid; }
    h1 { font-size: 18pt; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 6pt; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1pt; }
    h2 { font-size: 13pt; border-bottom: 1pt solid #333; padding-bottom: 4pt; margin: 20pt 0 12pt 0; text-transform: uppercase; }
    h3 { font-size: 11pt; margin: 14pt 0 8pt 0; }
    h4 { font-size: 10pt; margin: 10pt 0 6pt 0; }
    p { margin: 0 0 8pt 0; text-align: justify; hyphens: auto; }
    .doc-header { text-align: center; border-bottom: 2pt solid #333; padding-bottom: 15pt; margin-bottom: 20pt; }
    .doc-subtitle { font-size: 10pt; color: #555; margin: 5pt 0; }
    .doc-date { font-size: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt; }
    .premium-badge { display: inline-block; background: #2c5282; color: white; padding: 3pt 10pt; font-size: 9pt; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1pt; margin-top: 8pt; }
    .parties-section { margin: 15pt 0; }
    .party-block { margin: 10pt 0; padding-left: 20pt; }
    .party-role { font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 9pt; letter-spacing: 0.5pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; }
    .party-details-text { line-height: 1.6; }
    .definitions-list { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .definitions-list li { margin: 6pt 0; }
    .defined-term { font-weight: bold; }
    .clause { margin: 8pt 0; padding-left: 30pt; text-indent: -30pt; }
    .clause-num { display: inline-block; width: 28pt; font-weight: bold; }
    .data-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 12pt 0; font-size: 10pt; }
    .data-table th, .data-table td { border: 0.5pt solid #666; padding: 6pt 8pt; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
    .data-table th { background: #f5f5f5; font-weight: bold; font-size: 9pt; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .data-table td.label { width: 35%; font-weight: 500; background: #fafafa; }
    .data-table td.value { width: 65%; word-wrap: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .schedule { page-break-before: always; margin-top: 0; }
    .schedule-header { text-align: center; border: 1pt solid #333; padding: 10pt; margin-bottom: 15pt; background: #f8f8f8; }
    .schedule-header h2 { border: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    .schedule-title { font-size: 12pt; margin-top: 5pt; font-weight: normal; text-transform: none; }
    .signature-section { page-break-inside: avoid; margin-top: 30pt; }
    .signature-block { margin: 25pt 0; page-break-inside: avoid; }
    .signature-role { font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; font-size: 9pt; margin-bottom: 8pt; }
    .signature-name { margin-bottom: 20pt; }
    .signature-line { border-bottom: 1pt solid #333; width: 250pt; height: 25pt; }
    .signature-label { font-size: 9pt; color: #555; margin-top: 3pt; }
    .signature-date-line { border-bottom: 1pt solid #333; width: 150pt; display: inline-block; margin-left: 10pt; }
    .legal-notice { border: 1pt solid #333; padding: 10pt; margin: 12pt 0; background: #fffef5; page-break-inside: avoid; }
    .legal-notice-title { font-weight: bold; font-size: 10pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; text-transform: uppercase; }
    ul, ol { margin: 6pt 0 6pt 25pt; padding: 0; }
    li { margin: 4pt 0; }
    .wrap-text, .email-text, .address-text { word-wrap: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .doc-footer { margin-top: 30pt; padding-top: 10pt; border-top: 0.5pt solid #999; font-size: 8pt; color: #666; text-align: center; }
    .premium-section { border-left: 3pt solid #2c5282; padding-left: 12pt; margin: 15pt 0; }
    .premium-label { font-size: 8pt; color: #2c5282; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5pt; margin-bottom: 5pt; }
    @media print { .schedule { page-break-before: always; } .signature-section, .signature-block, .legal-notice, .schedule-header { page-break-inside: avoid; } h2, h3, h4 { page-break-after: avoid; } .data-table, .data-table tr { page-break-inside: avoid; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- COVER -->
  <div class="doc-header">
    <h1>Assured Shorthold Tenancy Agreement</h1>
    <div class="doc-subtitle">Housing Act 1988 (as amended)</div>
    <div class="doc-subtitle">England</div>
    <div class="premium-badge">Premium Edition</div>
    <div class="doc-date">Dated: <strong>{{formatUKDate agreement_date}}</strong></div>
  </div>

  <!-- 1. PARTIES -->
  <h2>1. Parties</h2>
  <div class="parties-section">
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{landlord_full_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{landlord_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{landlord_email}}</span> | {{landlord_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Landlord's Agent</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{agent_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{agent_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{agent_email}}</span> | {{agent_phone}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Tenant{{#if multiple_tenants}}s{{/if}}</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        {{#each tenants}}
        <strong>{{this.full_name}}</strong>{{#if this.dob}} (DOB: {{formatUKDate this.dob}}){{/if}}<br>
        <span class="email-text">{{this.email}}</span>{{#if this.phone}} | {{this.phone}}{{/if}}{{#unless @last}}<br><br>{{/unless}}
        {{/each}}
      </div>
    </div>

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="party-block">
      <div class="party-role">Guarantor</div>
      <div class="party-details-text">
        <strong>{{guarantor_name}}</strong><br>
        <span class="address-text">{{guarantor_address}}</span><br>
        <span class="email-text">{{guarantor_email}}</span> | {{guarantor_phone}}<br>
        {{#if guarantor_dob}}DOB: {{formatUKDate guarantor_dob}} | {{/if}}{{#if guarantor_relationship}}Relationship: {{guarantor_relationship}}{{/if}}
      </div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- 2. DEFINITIONS -->
  <h2>2. Definitions and Interpretation</h2>
  <p>In this Agreement, unless the context requires otherwise:</p>
  <ul class="definitions-list">
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Agreement"</span> means this tenancy agreement and all Schedules.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Landlord"</span> means {{landlord_full_name}} and successors in title.</li>
    {{#if agent_name}}<li><span class="defined-term">"Agent"</span> means {{agent_name}}, authorised to act on behalf of the Landlord.</li>{{/if}}
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Tenant"</span> means {{#each tenants}}{{this.full_name}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}}{{#if multiple_tenants}} (jointly and severally liable){{/if}}.</li>
    {{#if guarantor_name}}<li><span class="defined-term">"Guarantor"</span> means {{guarantor_name}}, whose obligations are set out in Section 9.</li>{{/if}}
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Property"</span> means {{property_address}} as described in Schedule 1.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Term"</span> means the {{#if is_fixed_term}}fixed term from {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}} to {{formatUKDate tenancy_end_date}}{{else}}periodic tenancy from {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}{{/if}} and any statutory continuation.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Rent"</span> means £{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}} payable as set out in Schedule 2.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Deposit"</span> means £{{deposit_amount}} protected in the Scheme as set out in Schedule 2.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Scheme"</span> means {{deposit_scheme_name}}.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Contents"</span> means items listed in any inventory.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Written Notice"</span> means notice in writing by hand, post, or email.</li>
    <li><span class="defined-term">"Working Day"</span> means any day other than Saturday, Sunday, or public holiday in England.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Words importing the singular include the plural. Where there is more than one Tenant, their obligations are joint and several.</p>

  <!-- 3. THE PROPERTY -->
  <h2>3. The Property</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.1</span> The Landlord lets to the Tenant the Property described in Schedule 1 for the Term, together with any Contents listed in the inventory.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.2</span> The Property is let for use as a private residential dwelling only.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">3.3</span> The Landlord warrants that all compliance certificates are valid and will be provided to the Tenant.</p>

  <!-- 4. THE TERM -->
  <h2>4. The Term</h2>
  {{#if is_fixed_term}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.1</span> The tenancy begins on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong> and ends on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_end_date}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.2</span> Upon expiry of the fixed term, unless either party serves notice, the tenancy continues as a statutory periodic tenancy.</p>
  {{else}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.1</span> The tenancy begins on <strong>{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}</strong> as a periodic (monthly) tenancy.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.2</span> The tenancy continues until terminated by proper notice.</p>
  {{/if}}
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.3</span> The Landlord may seek possession using Section 21 (minimum 2 months' notice) or Section 8 (fault-based) of the Housing Act 1988.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">4.4</span> The Tenant may end the tenancy by giving at least one month's written notice expiring on a rent due date.</p>

  <!-- 5. RENT -->
  <h2>5. Rent</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.1</span> The Tenant shall pay the Rent of <strong>£{{rent_amount}}</strong> per {{rent_period}} in advance on the <strong>{{rent_due_day}}</strong> of each {{rent_period}}.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.2</span> Payment shall be made by {{payment_method}} to the account in Schedule 2.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.3</span> The first payment is due on or before {{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}.</p>
  <div class="premium-section">
    <div class="premium-label">Premium: Late Payment</div>
    <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.4</span> If rent remains unpaid for {{#if grace_period_days}}{{grace_period_days}}{{else}}14{{/if}} days after the due date, interest accrues at {{#if late_payment_interest_rate}}{{late_payment_interest_rate}}%{{else}}3%{{/if}} above the Bank of England base rate per annum.</p>
    <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">5.5</span> The Tenant will receive a written reminder if rent is more than 7 days overdue. Persistent arrears may result in proceedings for possession.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 6. DEPOSIT -->
  <h2>6. Deposit</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.1</span> The Tenant has paid a Deposit of <strong>£{{deposit_amount}}</strong>.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.2</span> The Landlord will protect the Deposit in the Scheme within 30 days and provide prescribed information.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.3</span> The Deposit may be applied against unpaid rent, damage beyond fair wear and tear, cleaning costs, missing inventory items, or other sums due.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">6.4</span> Disputes may be referred to the Scheme's free ADR service.</p>

  <!-- 7. TENANT OBLIGATIONS -->
  <h2>7. Tenant Obligations</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.1</span> <strong>Rent:</strong> Pay the Rent on time and in full.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.2</span> <strong>Utilities:</strong> Pay charges for gas, electricity, water, council tax, and internet as set out in Schedule 3.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.3</span> <strong>Care:</strong> Keep the Property clean and in good condition, promptly report disrepair.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.4</span> <strong>Access:</strong> Allow the Landlord access with at least 24 hours' notice (except emergencies).</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.5</span> <strong>Use:</strong> Use the Property as a private residence only; comply with Schedule 5 (House Rules).</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.6</span> <strong>Nuisance:</strong> Not cause nuisance or disturbance to neighbours.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.7</span> <strong>Subletting:</strong> Not sublet or assign without prior written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.8</span> <strong>Alterations:</strong> Not make alterations without prior written consent.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.9</span> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Not invalidate the Landlord's insurance.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">7.10</span> <strong>End of Tenancy:</strong> Return the Property in original condition (fair wear and tear excepted), return all keys, provide forwarding address.</p>

  <!-- 8. LANDLORD OBLIGATIONS -->
  <h2>8. Landlord Obligations</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.1</span> <strong>Quiet Enjoyment:</strong> Allow the Tenant to occupy without interference.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.2</span> <strong>Repairs:</strong> Keep structure, exterior, and services (water, gas, electricity, heating, sanitation) in repair.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.3</span> <strong>Safety:</strong> Ensure valid Gas Safety Certificate, EICR, smoke and CO alarms, EPC rating E+.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.4</span> <strong>Deposit:</strong> Protect in scheme within 30 days; provide prescribed information.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.5</span> <strong>Documents:</strong> Provide How to Rent guide, EPC, Gas Safety Certificate, EICR.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.6</span> <strong>Insurance:</strong> Maintain buildings insurance.</p>
  <div class="premium-section">
    <div class="premium-label">Premium: Emergency Contacts</div>
    <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.7</span> The Landlord provides emergency contact details in Schedule 6 for use outside normal hours.</p>
  </div>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">8.8</span> <strong>Right to Rent:</strong> The Landlord confirms that the required Right to Rent checks have been carried out in accordance with the Immigration Act 2014 before the Tenant occupies the Property. Nothing in this Agreement makes the Tenant responsible for the Landlord's compliance with Right to Rent requirements.</p>

  {{#if guarantor_name}}
  <!-- 9. GUARANTOR AGREEMENT -->
  <h2>9. Guarantor Agreement</h2>
  <div class="legal-notice">
    <div class="legal-notice-title">Important Notice to Guarantor</div>
    <p>By signing this Agreement, the Guarantor makes a legally binding commitment. The Guarantor should seek independent legal advice before signing.</p>
  </div>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.1</span> The Guarantor guarantees the Tenant's obligations and is jointly and severally liable with the Tenant.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.2</span> If the Tenant fails to pay rent or breaches any term, the Guarantor shall pay or remedy the breach on demand.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.3</span> This guarantee continues throughout the tenancy including any periodic continuation.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.4</span> The Guarantor is liable for damage beyond fair wear and tear and any costs of enforcement.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.5</span> The Guarantor's liability is capped at {{#if guarantor_max_liability}}{{guarantor_max_liability}}{{else}}twelve (12) months' rent plus reasonable enforcement costs{{/if}}.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.6</span> The Guarantor will be released when tenancy ends and all obligations are satisfied, or upon the Landlord's written release.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">9.7</span> The Guarantor confirms they have been advised to seek independent legal advice.</p>
  {{/if}}

  <!-- 10. GENERAL PROVISIONS -->
  <h2>{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}. General Provisions</h2>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.1</span> This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.2</span> Variations must be in writing signed by all parties.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.3</span> This Agreement is governed by the laws of England and Wales.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.4</span> Notices may be served by hand, first-class post, or email.</p>
  <p class="clause"><span class="clause-num">{{#if guarantor_name}}10{{else}}9{{/if}}.5</span> If any provision is unenforceable, the remaining provisions continue in effect.</p>

  {{> statutory_acknowledgements jurisdiction="england" format="html" heading_style="h2"}}

  <!-- SIGNATURES -->
  <div class="signature-section">
    <h2>Signatures</h2>
    <p>By signing below, the parties confirm they have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Agreement and all Schedules.</p>

    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Landlord</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{landlord_full_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>

    {{#if agent_name}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Agent</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{agent_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}

    {{#each tenants}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Tenant {{add @index 1}}</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{this.full_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/each}}

    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <div class="signature-block">
      <div class="signature-role">Guarantor</div>
      <div class="signature-name">Name: {{guarantor_name}}</div>
      <div class="signature-line"></div>
      <div class="signature-label">Signature</div>
      <div style="margin-top: 10pt;">Date: <span class="signature-date-line"></span></div>
    </div>
    {{/if}}
  </div>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 1: PROPERTY -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 1</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Property Details</div>
    </div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Address</td><td class="value address-text">{{property_address}}</td></tr>
      {{#if property_type}}<tr><td class="label">Type</td><td class="value">{{property_type}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_bedrooms}}<tr><td class="label">Bedrooms</td><td class="value">{{number_of_bedrooms}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if furnished_status}}<tr><td class="label">Furnished</td><td class="value">{{furnished_status}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if council_tax_band}}<tr><td class="label">Council Tax</td><td class="value">Band {{council_tax_band}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if epc_rating}}<tr><td class="label">EPC</td><td class="value">{{epc_rating}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if parking_available}}<tr><td class="label">Parking</td><td class="value">{{#if parking_details}}{{parking_details}}{{else}}Included{{/if}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    <h3>Compliance</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Gas Safety</td><td class="value">{{#if gas_safety_certificate}}Valid{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">EICR</td><td class="value">{{#if electrical_safety_certificate}}Valid{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">EPC</td><td class="value">{{#if epc_rating}}{{epc_rating}}{{else}}To be provided{{/if}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Smoke/CO Alarms</td><td class="value">Fitted as required</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h3>Documents Provided</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>How to Rent guide (current version)</li>
      <li>Energy Performance Certificate</li>
      <li>Gas Safety Certificate</li>
      <li>Electrical Installation Condition Report</li>
      <li>Deposit prescribed information (within 30 days)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 2: RENT & DEPOSIT -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 2</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Rent and Deposit</div>
    </div>
    <h3>Part A: Rent</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Amount</td><td class="value">£{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Due Date</td><td class="value">{{rent_due_day}} of each {{rent_period}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Method</td><td class="value">{{payment_method}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">First Payment</td><td class="value">{{#if first_payment_date}}{{formatUKDate first_payment_date}}{{else}}{{formatUKDate tenancy_start_date}}{{/if}}</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h4>Bank Details</h4>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Account Name</td><td class="value">{{#if bank_account_name}}{{bank_account_name}}{{else}}{{landlord_full_name}}{{/if}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Sort Code</td><td class="value">{{bank_sort_code}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Account Number</td><td class="value">{{bank_account_number}}</td></tr>
    </table>
    <h3>Part B: Deposit</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Amount</td><td class="value">£{{deposit_amount}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Scheme</td><td class="value">{{deposit_scheme_name}}</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="legal-notice">
      <div class="legal-notice-title">Deposit Protection</div>
      <p>Protected within 30 days. Disputes referred to ADR service. Deductions only for: unpaid rent, damage beyond fair wear and tear, missing items, cleaning, unreturned keys.</p>
    </div>
    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <h3>Part C: Guarantor</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Name</td><td class="value">{{guarantor_name}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Address</td><td class="value address-text">{{guarantor_address}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Contact</td><td class="value email-text">{{guarantor_email}} | {{guarantor_phone}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="label">Max Liability</td><td class="value">{{#if guarantor_max_liability}}{{guarantor_max_liability}}{{else}}12 months' rent + costs{{/if}}</td></tr>
    </table>
    {{/if}}
  </section>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 3: UTILITIES -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 3</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Utilities and Services</div>
    </div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><th>Utility</th><th>Responsibility</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Council Tax</td><td>{{#if council_tax_responsibility}}{{council_tax_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td><td>{{#if council_tax_band}}Band {{council_tax_band}}{{/if}}</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Gas</td><td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td><td>Register with supplier</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Electricity</td><td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td><td>Register with supplier</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Water</td><td>{{#if utilities_responsibility}}{{utilities_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td><td></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Internet</td><td>{{#if internet_responsibility}}{{internet_responsibility}}{{else}}Tenant{{/if}}</td><td></td></tr>
      <tr><td>TV Licence</td><td>Tenant</td><td>If required</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Buildings Insurance</td><td>Landlord</td><td>Tenant arranges contents</td></tr>
    </table>
    {{#if meter_reading_gas}}{{#if meter_reading_electric}}
    <h3>Meter Readings</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      {{#if meter_reading_gas}}<tr><td class="label">Gas</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_gas}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if meter_reading_electric}}<tr><td class="label">Electricity</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_electric}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if meter_reading_water}}<tr><td class="label">Water</td><td class="value">{{meter_reading_water}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    {{/if}}{{/if}}
  </section>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 4: INVENTORY -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 4</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Inventory and Condition</div>
    </div>
    {{#if inventory_attached}}<p>Detailed inventory attached separately.</p>{{else}}<p>Tenant should photograph property condition at start.</p>{{/if}}
    <h3>Keys</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      {{#if number_of_front_door_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Front Door</td><td class="value">{{number_of_front_door_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_back_door_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Back Door</td><td class="value">{{number_of_back_door_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if access_cards_fobs}}<tr><td class="label">Fobs/Cards</td><td class="value">{{access_cards_fobs}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if number_of_mailbox_keys}}<tr><td class="label">Mailbox</td><td class="value">{{number_of_mailbox_keys}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    <p>All keys must be returned. {{#if key_replacement_cost}}Replacement cost: £{{key_replacement_cost}}.{{/if}}</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 5: HOUSE RULES -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 5</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">House Rules</div>
    </div>
    <h3>Pets</h3>
    <table class="data-table"><tr><td class="label">Permitted</td><td class="value">{{#if pets_allowed}}Yes{{#if approved_pets}} ({{approved_pets}}){{/if}}{{else}}No (consent required){{/if}}</td></tr></table>
    <h3>Smoking</h3>
    <table class="data-table"><tr><td class="label">Permitted</td><td class="value">{{#if smoking_allowed}}Outdoors only{{else}}No{{/if}}</td></tr></table>
    <h3>Subletting</h3>
    <p>Not permitted without prior written consent. No short-term letting platforms.</p>
    <h3>Quiet Hours</h3>
    <p>Keep noise reasonable, especially 11pm-7am.</p>
    {{#if has_garden}}<h3>Garden</h3><p>Tenant maintains in reasonable condition.</p>{{/if}}
    <h3>Alterations</h3>
    <p>Not permitted without consent. Minor fixtures may be allowed.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- SCHEDULE 6: EMERGENCY CONTACTS (PREMIUM) -->
  <section class="schedule">
    <div class="schedule-header">
      <h2>Schedule 6</h2>
      <div class="schedule-title">Emergency Contacts (Premium)</div>
    </div>
    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><td class="label">Landlord/Agent</td><td class="value">{{#if emergency_landlord_phone}}{{emergency_landlord_phone}}{{else}}{{landlord_phone}}{{/if}}</td></tr>
      {{#if emergency_plumber_phone}}<tr><td class="label">Plumber</td><td class="value">{{emergency_plumber_phone}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if emergency_electrician_phone}}<tr><td class="label">Electrician</td><td class="value">{{emergency_electrician_phone}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if emergency_gas_engineer_phone}}<tr><td class="label">Gas Engineer</td><td class="value">{{emergency_gas_engineer_phone}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if emergency_locksmith_phone}}<tr><td class="label">Locksmith</td><td class="value">{{emergency_locksmith_phone}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    <h3>Shut-Off Locations</h3>
    <table class="data-table">
      {{#if water_shutoff_location}}<tr><td class="label">Water</td><td class="value">{{water_shutoff_location}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if electricity_fuse_box_location}}<tr><td class="label">Electricity</td><td class="value">{{electricity_fuse_box_location}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
      {{#if gas_shutoff_location}}<tr><td class="label">Gas</td><td class="value">{{gas_shutoff_location}}</td></tr>{{/if}}
    </table>
    <h3>In Emergency</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Gas leak: Call National Gas Emergency 0800 111 999, open windows, do not use switches</li>
      <li>Water leak: Turn off at stopcock, then call landlord/agent</li>
      <li>Power failure: Check fuse box, call landlord/agent if not resolved</li>
      <li>Fire: Evacuate, call 999, then notify landlord</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <div class="doc-footer">
    <p>Premium Assured Shorthold Tenancy Agreement &mdash; England</p>
    <p>Generated: {{formatUKDate current_date}} | Reference: {{#if case_id}}{{case_id}}{{else}}{{document_id}}{{/if}}</p>
    <p>Compliant with Housing Act 1988, Deregulation Act 2015, Tenant Fees Act 2019, Immigration Act 2014</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
